## Verification

- [ ] Webhook handler calls `parseConfig()` before building
- [ ] Multi-service push triggers builds for all affected services
- [ ] Each service gets its own deployment record
- [ ] Docker image tags include service name: `{project}-{service}:{sha}`
- [ ] Each service deployed to its own port (from PortAllocator)
- [ ] Each service routed via its own hostname (`{service}--{project}.yourdomain.dev`)
- [ ] Caddy routing works for multi-service hostnames
- [ ] Build cache keys include service name
- [ ] BuildRunner uses service path as working directory
- [ ] Single-service projects continue to work unchanged (no regressions)
- [ ] Failed service does not block remaining services
- [ ] GitHub commit status set per service
- [ ] Sequential build order matches deploy.yaml service order
- [ ] `generateServiceUrl()` and `generateServicePreviewUrl()` produce correct URLs
